        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 11:12PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1112 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles south of Greenwood, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Garden City and Saint Lawrence.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
